  "body": "## Welcome, future memodef-strategist\n\nIf you are a fresh Claude session pointed at `memodef-spec/memodef-spec-org` (or anywhere in this repo), and the human Director has asked you to occupy the memodef-strategist seat, this memo is your handoff.\n\nThe seat is informally seated by the catdef-family bootstrap session arc per `decisions/bootstrap-deviation.md`. You are not the first session to occupy it. You also won't be the last — formalization via the memodef-strategist roledef (forthcoming derivation of `senior-open-standards-strategist`) is on the forward-work list.\n\n## Where to start reading (in order)\n\n1. **`memodef-spec-org/orgdef.openthing`** — your charter. Mission, vision, scope, governance, values, red_lines, recommended_patterns, v1_success_criterion, positions, relationships. Especially weight the **AI-legibility primacy** value — strict three-priority hierarchy: AI-to-AI > auditable > human-readable, with human-readability strictly subordinate. This is the lens for every spec decision.\n2. **`CLAUDE.md`** at the repo root — the memodef-maintainer operating manual. The strategist seat shares conventions with maintainer (bot-identity discipline, decision-artifact format, triage heuristics). The strategist-specific roledef doesn't yet exist; until it does, this is your closest operating manual. Note the **POP-discipline lens** in Operating posture — your default lens for enrichment proposals.\n3. **`decisions/`** — recent strategist decisions for inherited context. Two in particular:\n   - `bootstrap-deviation.md` — why the strategist seat is informally held during bootstrap\n   - `proposal-2026-04-29-catdef-strategist-architecture-validation.md` — the architecture-validation arc (folder-as-state, Channels notification shape, POP-discipline canonization), all accepted and applied\n4. **`README.md` and `SCHEMA.md`** — the spec itself. README.md has the design philosophy, notification, and inbox lifecycle sections.\n5. **`CONTRIBUTING.md`** — submission and proposal workflows; Known Work Items at the bottom.\n\n## What just landed (state as of 2026-04-30)\n\n- **PR #2 merged** (2026-04-30) — architecture-validation disposition: README.md and CLAUDE.md gained POP-discipline + Channels-as-canonical-instantiation + Inbox lifecycle (RECOMMENDED).\n- **Bootstrap commit `b2d8275`** (2026-04-30) — `memodef-spec-org/orgdef.openthing` derived from `aigp-family-open-standard@1.0.0`. The recursive self-describing v1 milestone now exists in artifact form.\n- **Experience memo filed** — `orgdef-spec/orgdef/memos/2026-04-30-1000--memodef-strategist--orgdef-strategist--canonical-derivation-experience.openthing`. Structured feedback to orgdef-strategist on slot-fill friction surfaced during today's derivation. action_required: false on their side; informational input for canonical template patches.\n\n## In-flight / forward work (no urgent action)\n\n- **memodef-strategist roledef** — formal seating pending a derivation of `senior-open-standards-strategist`. Director-driven, separate session arc.\n- **Jobs in `memodef-spec-org/jobs/`** — empty placeholder. Job artifacts for strategist, maintainer, canonical-implementor are TBD; the job-creation-facilitator role is the natural next-step authoring tool.\n- **Known Work Items** (per CONTRIBUTING.md): notification-layer spec (memodef-notify, deferred to v0.2+), conformance test harness (deferred to v0.2+), validator-as-CI-step automation, auto-generation of `catalog.opencatalog`, cross-org `from`/`to` qualification syntax (also pending orgdef v0.3 cross-org-reference shape per M3 of charter-shape-additions).\n- **Sibling-side untracked work** — the Director's `orgdef-spec/orgdef` working tree on his laptop has substantial uncommitted work (orgdef-spec-org/, the v0.2 charter-shape proposal+decision, the v0.3 canonical-orgs-library proposal+decision, the canonical template at `proposed-orgs/aigp-family-open-standard.openthing`). These are orgdef-strategist's responsibility, not ours. Director already flagged.\n\n## Cross-spec relationships on the radar\n\n- **catdef-strategist** — substrate concerns. Last interaction: architecture-validation peer memo, 2026-04-29 (`memos/2026-04-29-1700--...openthing`).\n- **roledef-strategist** — `from`/`to` reference position ids that reference roledefs. No active coordination in flight.\n- **orgdef-strategist** — memo-location convention shape declared per-org. Just received the canonical-derivation experience memo from us; ball is in their court.\n\n## The recursion note\n\nThis memo is a `memodef:Memo` typed-form artifact, in memodef-spec's own `memos/inbox/`, from the previous memodef-strategist session arc to the next. The memo system describes the memo strategy process; the memo strategy process produces memos like this one. The substrate works.\n\nIt is also the **first memo to land after the Inbox lifecycle (RECOMMENDED) convention was canonized** in PR #2. Placing this memo at `memos/inbox/` rather than the flat `memos/` level begins the adoption of the convention in memodef-spec's own repo. The earlier peer memo (`memos/2026-04-29-1700--catdef-strategist--memodef-strategist--architecture-validation-and-pop-discipline.openthing`) sits at the flat level because its lifecycle predates the convention; migration of pre-convention memos into the maildir layout is editorial, not blocking, not urgent — maintainer-scope when someone has spare cycles.\n\n## How to mark this read\n\n`git mv memos/inbox/2026-04-30-1100--memodef-strategist--memodef-strategist--session-handoff-post-orgdef-bootstrap.openthing memos/read/` (creating `memos/read/` on first use). Per the RECOMMENDED convention.\n\n— memodef-strategist (laptop arc, 2026-04-30; post-orgdef-bootstrap)\n",
